Oh, I guarantee he'll be watching.

172
00:09:57,520 --> 00:10:00,640
先生  您得接一下
Sir? I think you should take this.

173
00:10:00,740 --> 00:10:01,800
失陪
Excuse me.

174
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:06,200
你好  议员女士
Hello, Congresswoman.

175
00:10:18,790 --> 00:10:20,990
抱歉来晚了  请坐
Sorry for the delay. Please sit down.

176
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:24,320
你收到耳环了吗
Did you get the earrings?

177
00:10:24,620 --> 00:10:25,890
是的  谢谢
I did. Thank you.

178
00:10:25,890 --> 00:10:27,740
我母亲的  两克拉钻石
My mother's. Two-carat diamonds.

179
00:10:27,740 --> 00:10:28,740
今晚戴吧
For tonight.

180
00:10:28,790 --> 00:10:30,450
没什么比得上钻石耳环了
There's nothing quite like diamond earrings.

181
00:10:30,450 --> 00:10:31,400
我们开始吧
Shall we begin?

182
00:10:33,090 --> 00:10:35,740
今年  我们要改变一下出场方式
Uh, this year, we're handling the arrival a bit differently.

183
00:10:35,740 --> 00:10:38,740
您将先被护送去圆形大厅与领导层合影
You'll be escorted to the rotunda for a photo op with the leadership

184
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:41,040
然后再去等候室
before going to the holding room.

185
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:42,390
我不需要去等候室
I don't need to go to the holding room.

186
00:10:42,390 --> 00:10:44,390
你直接带我去大厅吧
You can take me directly to the gallery.

187
00:10:44,390 --> 00:10:46,990
没关系  都听第一夫人的
Yes, that's fine. Whatever the First Lady prefers.

188
00:10:46,990 --> 00:10:49,040
之后我们需要分两个车队
And we'll need two separate motorcades after.

189
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:51,280
我要直接去机场
I'll be going straight to the airport.

190
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:53,570
-那就两个车队  -是  先生
- Two motorcades, then. - Yes, sir.

191
00:10:54,190 --> 00:10:56,060
我想向你们汇报一下特别来宾名单
I'd like to brief you on the list of special guests attending--

192
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:58,070
看上去没什么问题
This all seems pretty straightforward.

193
00:10:58,070 --> 00:10:59,010
如果你觉得没问题我也没问题
I'm good if you are.

194
00:10:59,010 --> 00:11:01,380
嗯  没问题  多谢你了
Yes, I'm fine. Thank you so very much.

195
00:11:06,430 --> 00:11:07,620
你有空吗
Do you have a moment?

196
00:11:10,970 --> 00:11:12,040
伊丽莎白怎么样了
How's Elizabeth?

197
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:14,070
她让我代她问好
She sends her regards.

198
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:15,650
当然了
I'll bet she does.

199
00:11:15,650 --> 00:11:16,870
竞选呢
And the campaign?

200
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:20,360
还在试探
Still exploring viability.

201
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:22,250
桃瑞丝还没答应吗
Doris isn't on board yet?

202
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:23,350
回头就知道了
Uh, we'll see.

203
00:11:24,030 --> 00:11:25,380
你给了她什么
What have you offered her?

204
00:11:26,750 --> 00:11:29,500
我想先跟莉安策划一个稳妥的竞选策略
Well, I want to put together a solid campaign strategy with LeAnn

205
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,850
再跟她二次接触
before engaging her again.

206
00:11:31,850 --> 00:11:33,660
如果你需要我帮忙  就告诉我
Well, if you need my help, let me know.

207
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,720
我当党鞭时  我们关系很好
She and I were very close when I was whip.

208
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:38,700
-你的事够多了  -不麻烦的
- You've got a lot on your plate. - No, it's no trouble at all.

209
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:40,300
我再找你吧
I'll let you know.

210
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,040
今晚见
See you tonight.

211
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,100
可以开始准备了吗  先生
You ready to prep, sir?

212
00:11:59,100 --> 00:12:00,710
我要做些改动
I need to make some changes.

213
00:12:01,350 --> 00:12:02,240
我去叫讲稿撰写人
I'll call the speech writers.

214
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:04,670
不用  我自己来  去把克丽丝塔找来
No, I wanna do these myself. And track down Calista.

215
00:12:04,670 --> 00:12:06,500
我们还得再加一名宾客
We have to make room for one more guest.

216
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:07,450
是  先生
Yes, sir.

217
00:12:34,030 --> 00:12:35,020
怎么回事
What's that?

218
00:12:36,050 --> 00:12:37,570
我要把文身洗掉
I'm having it removed.

219
00:12:40,230 --> 00:12:41,980
太可惜了  我挺喜欢呢
Well, that's too bad. I liked it.

220
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,510
该向前看了
Hmm, time to move on.

221
00:12:44,850 --> 00:12:45,920
你想放下什么
From what?

222
00:12:47,590 --> 00:12:49,690
需要文身的我
From the me that needed a tattoo.

223
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:52,080
我没多少时间
I don't have much time.

224
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:55,010
你什么时候得去国会大厦
When do you have to be at the Capitol?

225
00:12:55,490 --> 00:12:56,830
不到一小时后
Less than an hour.

226
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,660
-威士忌还是伏特加  -伏特加
- Whiskey or vodka? - Vodka.

227
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:06,690
你对桃瑞丝·琼斯有多了解
How well do you know Doris Jones?

228
00:13:08,470 --> 00:13:10,950
见过她几次  不怎么了解
Oh, uh, met her a few times. I don't know her that well, though.

229
00:13:11,550 --> 00:13:13,390
-怎么  -她女儿  西莉娅
- Why? - Her daughter, Celia,

230
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:15,120
希望我帮他们弄到拨款
wants me to help them get appropriations

231
00:13:15,230 --> 00:13:17,040
筹建一家乳腺癌诊所
for a breast cancer clinic.

232
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:20,790
作为回报  他们愿用德州的钱资助我的竞选
In return, they want to pad my campaign with Texas money.

233
00:13:20,790 --> 00:13:22,780
-多少  -三百万
- How much? - Three million.

234
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:24,670
可能还不止
To start.

235
00:13:25,030 --> 00:13:27,100
她的选区才没那么多钱
Her district doesn't have that kind of money.

236
00:13:27,100 --> 00:13:29,990
西莉娅说他们的捐助人是30区以外的
Celia says they're courting donors from outside the 30th.

237
00:13:29,990 --> 00:13:31,330
但我一个助手
But one of my aides

238
00:13:31,330 --> 00:13:34,080
听说克莱尔·安德伍德和莉安·哈维
heard that Claire Underwood and LeAnn Harvey

239
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,750
今天去了琼斯的办公室
were in Jones' office today.

240
00:13:39,290 --> 00:13:41,360
莉安我认识
LeAnn's someone I know.

241
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:45,330
格兰顿-希尔几年前想把她挖来
Glendon Hill was courting her a few years ago.

242
00:13:45,660 --> 00:13:47,120
她拒绝了你吗
Did she turn you down?

243
00:13:47,890 --> 00:13:49,220
我们请不起她
We couldn't afford her.

244
00:13:51,370 --> 00:13:53,830
我知道你已经金盆洗手了  但这笔钱不是小数
Look, I know you're out of the game, but this is a lot of money.

245
00:13:53,830 --> 00:13:56,650
如果是真  能帮我大忙  如果不是...
If it's legit, it could really help me. But if it's not, I--

246
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:58,860
我去跟莉安谈谈  看能问出什么来
I'll talk to LeAnn and see what I can find out.

247
00:14:00,660 --> 00:14:01,620
给
Here.

248
00:14:03,850 --> 00:14:05,940
我想先尝你
I want to taste you first.

249
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:05,600
下面是特别报道
This is a special report.

250
00:15:05,770 --> 00:15:08,410
弗兰西斯·安德伍德总统向国会联席会议
President Francis Underwood's State of the Union address

251
00:15:08,410 --> 00:15:10,090
发表国情咨文讲话
to a joint session of Congress.

252
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:14,760
今晚  世界的眼睛都盯着华盛顿
Tonight the eyes of the world are on Washington.

253
00:15:14,970 --> 00:15:17,940
安德伍德总统几分钟后就将上台
President Underwood will take the stage in just a few minutes...

254
00:15:19,540 --> 00:15:21,040
把食物拿走
Take the food away.

255
00:15:21,270 --> 00:15:22,940
您午饭就没吃  黑尔太太
You didn't eat your lunch, Mrs. Hale.

256
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:24,900
我不舒服
Yeah, well, I didn't feel well.

257
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,730
那您就更该吃点晚饭了  您的药
Then you really should eat dinner. Your medication--

258
00:15:26,730 --> 00:15:28,850
别让我再说一遍了  迈克尔
Please don't make me ask you again, Michael.

259
00:15:28,850 --> 00:15:31,860
拿走  这味儿熏得我难受
Just take it away. The smell of it is making me ill.

260
00:15:32,830 --> 00:15:33,810
是  夫人
Yes, ma'am.

261
00:15:36,930 --> 00:15:40,940
女士们先生们  美国第一夫人
Ladies and gentlemen, the First Lady of the United States.

262
00:15:57,860 --> 00:16:00,950
-西莉娅  -谢谢你的安排
- Celia. - Thank you so much for arranging this.

263
00:16:01,050 --> 00:16:03,530
能坐在你旁边太荣幸了
It's a big honor to be sitting next to you.

264
00:16:18,710 --> 00:16:23,190
议长先生  有请美国总统
Mr. Speaker, the President of the United States.

265
00:17:03,660 --> 00:17:05,820
在这里看国情咨文真有意思
Interesting place to watch the SOTU.

266
00:17:06,990 --> 00:17:10,540
这样更好玩  跟人民大众在一起
It's more fun this way. You know, hanging with the hoi polloi.

267
00:17:11,790 --> 00:17:13,380
你为什么来华府
So, what brings you to D.C.?

268
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,590
国会都到齐了  适合揽活儿干
Well, all of Congress in town, it's good for hustling work.

269
00:17:16,590 --> 00:17:19,430
你什么时候揽过活儿  你从来都是拒绝别人
Since when do you hustle? You turn people away.

270
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,320
你怎么知道我在这儿
How'd you know I was in town?

271
00:17:21,530 --> 00:17:24,080
我虽然退休了  但还是眼观六路耳听八方
I might be retired, but I still have my ear to the ground.

272
00:17:24,850 --> 00:17:28,640
是真的喽  伟大的雷米·丹顿解甲归田了
So that's true? The great Remy Danton has hung up his jersey?

273
00:17:29,910 --> 00:17:31,400
我从未这么痛快过
I've never felt better.

274
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:34,490
-你不是来跟我寒暄的吧  -不是
- Don't tell me this is a social visit. - No.

275
00:17:34,820 --> 00:17:37,090
-如果不是为公事  -是公事
- Well, if it isn't business... - It's business.

276
00:17:37,090 --> 00:17:38,690
-各位国会议员  -好吧
- Members of Congress... - Okay.

277
00:17:38,690 --> 00:17:40,160
-我十分荣幸  -那么
- ...I have the high privilege... - So...

278
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,800
-等等  节目开始了  -为各位请出
- Oh, hold on. The show is starting. - ...of presenting to you,

279
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,830
美国总统
the President of the United States.

280
00:17:56,770 --> 00:17:57,770
谢谢
Thank you.

281
00:17:59,410 --> 00:18:00,620
非常感谢
Thank you so much.

282
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:06,160
谢谢  议长先生  副总统先生
Thank you. Mr. Speaker, Mr. Vice President,

283
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:09,200
各位国会议员  我的美国同胞们
members of Congress, my fellow Americans.

284
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:10,960
一年前
One year ago,

285
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:14,080
我第一次做这番讲话
when I gave this address for the first time,

286
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:18,270
当时我国处于完全不同的一个时期
it was during a very different period for our country.

287
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:22,040
我国正在从一起政治丑闻和
Our nation was recovering from a political scandal

288
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:24,570
与中国的贸易危机中走出来
and a trade crisis with China.

289
00:18:24,940 --> 00:18:29,160
而你们面前的  是一位未经过选举的总统
Before you stood a president no one had elected.

290
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:32,450
但现在  那个人依然站在你们面前
But that same man stands before you now,

291
00:18:32,450 --> 00:18:34,410
而黑暗时期已经过去
and the darkness is behind us.

292
00:18:34,410 --> 00:18:38,010
国家现在情势大好  前途愈发光明
The state of the union is bright, and getting brighter.

293
00:18:45,710 --> 00:18:47,810
我们遭遇过挑战  没错
We've had our challenges, yes.

294
00:18:47,820 --> 00:18:49,640
尤其是跟俄罗斯
Particularly with Russia.

295
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:52,430
的确有些很紧张的时刻
There were some tense moments, to be sure,

296
00:18:52,430 --> 00:18:55,270
但我们还是克服了那些紧张
and yet we overcame those tensions.

297
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:58,620
佩特罗夫总统让我们继续建立信任
President Petrov let us continue to build trust

298
00:18:58,620 --> 00:19:02,330
并表现出我们已从去年的经历中吸取了教训
and show that we've learned from our experiences last year.

299
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:05,370
我个人想感谢第一夫人
And I'd personally like to acknowledge the First Lady,

300
00:19:05,370 --> 00:19:09,400
她为修复两国关系带了路
who led the way in repairing those burned bridges.

301
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,990
她得到的掌声比总统还多
She's getting more applause than the president.

302
00:19:19,690 --> 00:19:21,080
对你是好事吧
Good for you, isn't it?

303
00:19:22,830 --> 00:19:24,560
好厉害的客户
Quite a high-profile client.

304
00:19:25,160 --> 00:19:26,230
谁告诉你的
Who told you that?

305
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,600
只是一猜
Just a guess.

306
00:19:28,220 --> 00:19:29,740
不  你猜错了
No, you guessed wrong.

307
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:35,140
你知道有财大气粗的德州捐助人
So what do you know about big Texas donors...

308
00:19:35,660 --> 00:19:37,510
就为了达拉斯一个穷选区
who care enough about a poor Dallas district

309
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:40,350
会给加州的竞选捐钱吗
to donate money to a campaign in California?

310
00:19:40,520 --> 00:19:42,280
我没听说过
That went right over my head.

311
00:19:43,170 --> 00:19:46,410
第一夫人去了达拉斯  你当时也在那儿
First Lady was in Dallas. You were in Dallas.

312
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:47,640
第一夫人来了这儿
The First Lady is here.

313
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:48,800
你也来了
Now you're here.

314
00:19:49,540 --> 00:19:53,590
我觉得你是太闲了  雷米
I think you have far too much time on your hands, Remy.

315
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,230
这笔钱上到处是你的痕迹
Your fingerprints are all over this money.

316
00:20:04,430 --> 00:20:06,530
你现在为杰姬·夏普工作了
You're working for Jackie Sharp now?

317
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:09,330
不  只是朋友
No. Just friends.

318
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:13,920
-只是朋友吗  -嗯
- Just friends, huh? - Yeah.

319
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:18,900
我觉得她身上也到处是你的痕迹
I think your fingerprints are all over her.

320
00:20:22,170 --> 00:20:23,280
这样如何
How about this?

321
00:20:24,710 --> 00:20:28,120
你别来刺探我的事
You don't poke around in my shit...

322
00:20:28,700 --> 00:20:30,760
我就不去刺探你的
and I won't poke around in yours.

323
00:20:31,820 --> 00:20:34,920
见到你很高兴  雷米  别退休就变怂了
It was good to see you, Remy. Don't get too soft in retirement.

324
00:20:38,710 --> 00:20:40,020
一般来说
Now, it's considered uncouth

325
00:20:40,020 --> 00:20:42,390
正在进行竞选的总统
for a president who's in the midst of a campaign,

326
00:20:42,390 --> 00:20:45,990
不该直接谈论即将到来的竞选  但今晚
to talk directly about the upcoming election, but tonight,

327
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:47,310
我觉得我必须谈
I feel compelled.

328
00:20:47,310 --> 00:20:50,020
因为我们选民即将在
Because the votes our electorate casts

329
00:20:50,130 --> 00:20:53,780
目前的初选和11月的大选中投的票
during the current primaries and the general election in November

330
00:20:53,790 --> 00:20:58,270
将对在座的各位有深远的影响
will have a profound impact on everyone in this room.

331
00:20:58,270 --> 00:21:03,490
有些人  包括我  可能将失业
Some of us, myself included, may find ourselves out of a job.

332
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:05,910
如果我们想保住工作
If we want to keep our jobs,

333
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:08,310
我们就得聆听美国民众的声音
we have to listen to the American people.

334
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:11,480
我们就得更加努力  说到做到
We have to work harder! We have to deliver!

335
00:21:15,830 --> 00:21:18,350
就像桃瑞丝·琼斯
Just like Doris Jones.

336
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:22,640
她已经在国会任职了34年
She has kept her job in Congress for 34 years

337
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:26,740
因为她从未向逆境低过头
because she never relented in the face of adversity.

338
00:21:26,740 --> 00:21:30,910
事实上  就在今天  她还为一家她已经争取了
In fact, just today, she called me about a breast cancer clinic

339
00:21:30,910 --> 00:21:34,250
十年的乳腺癌诊所给我打了电话
she has been fighting for over the past decade.

340
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,930
她的计划很大胆
Now, her plan is bold.

341
00:21:36,030 --> 00:21:39,520
将退伍军人医院扩张  向普通民众开放
A VA hospital expansion open to the general public,

342
00:21:39,520 --> 00:21:41,120
由联邦资金资助
financed by federal money.

343
00:21:41,130 --> 00:21:46,140
这一大胆计划能通过科普  筛查
A bold plan that will significantly increase successful diagnoses

344
00:21:46,140 --> 00:21:50,600
和可负担医保  大幅提升确诊和治疗的成功率
and treatment through education, screenings, and affordable care.

