You see, all he needed was a little motivation.

521
00:31:47,050 --> 00:31:49,060
所以我可以给克莱尔时间
So I'll give Claire some time.

522
00:31:49,670 --> 00:31:50,430
但为了她好
But for her sake,

523
00:31:50,430 --> 00:31:51,820
希望她能在我拿出斧子之前
I hope she comes out of her tree

524
00:31:51,820 --> 00:31:54,000
就从她的树上下来
before I have to bring out my ax.

525
00:32:05,750 --> 00:32:08,670
他要我等着竞选参议员
He wants me to hold off for Senate.

526
00:32:09,470 --> 00:32:11,070
我告诉他我会考虑的
I told him I would think about it.

527
00:32:11,070 --> 00:32:14,410
-那么结束了吗  -不  没结束
- So it's over? - Oh, no, it's not over.

528
00:32:14,570 --> 00:32:16,960
他在全国电视上表示支持西莉娅
He endorsed Celia on national television.

529
00:32:16,970 --> 00:32:18,410
别去想30选区了
Forget the 30th.

530
00:32:19,070 --> 00:32:21,940
我们得往大想  就在本轮
We need to think bigger. This cycle.

531
00:32:24,970 --> 00:32:27,730
那我们得好好谈谈我的酬金问题了
Then we need to talk seriously about my compensation.

532
00:32:34,230 --> 00:32:35,800
-接通了吗  -是  先生
- He on? - Yes, sir.

533
00:32:44,290 --> 00:32:45,320
我准备好了
I'm ready.

534
00:32:45,410 --> 00:32:46,890
我这就给您接  先生
I'll connect you now, sir.

535
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:49,380
佩特罗夫总统  您现在在跟总统通话了
President Petrov, you are now on with the president.

536
00:32:49,380 --> 00:32:50,950
晚上好  总统先生
Good evening, Mr. President.

537
00:32:51,550 --> 00:32:53,390
早上好  总统先生
Good morning, Mr. President.

538
00:32:53,390 --> 00:32:54,780
你的讲话很棒
Your speech was good.

539
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:56,480
或许有点太...
Perhaps, a bit too...

540
00:32:57,030 --> 00:32:58,340
乐观了
optimistic, hmm?

541
00:32:58,340 --> 00:33:00,230
我说的关于俄罗斯的话都是真心的
I meant what I said about Russia.

542
00:33:00,230 --> 00:33:02,930
那只是空谈  没多大意义
It's just words. They mean very little.

543
00:33:02,930 --> 00:33:05,110
我愿意用实际行动支持我的言论
I'm willing to back them up with action.

544
00:33:05,110 --> 00:33:06,600
首先  我们该谈谈救市计划
First, we should talk about a bailout.

545
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:09,300
我愿意跟国际货币基金组织合作  帮你拿到所需
I'm willing to work with the IMF to get you what you need.

546
00:33:09,370 --> 00:33:11,810
其次  作为示好
And second, as a gesture of good faith,

547
00:33:11,810 --> 00:33:14,370
我们愿把伊戈尔·米尔金还给俄罗斯
we'd like to return Igor Milkin to Russia.

548
00:33:14,370 --> 00:33:15,920
你早该送他回来了
You should've done so already.

549
00:33:15,920 --> 00:33:18,370
我需要你保证他会得到审判
I need your assurances he'll get a trial.

550
00:33:18,370 --> 00:33:20,970
-你在乎伊戈尔·米尔金干吗  -我不在乎
- What do you care about Igor Milkin? - I don't.

551
00:33:20,980 --> 00:33:22,120
你就是把他送去西伯利亚
You can send him to Siberia

552
00:33:22,120 --> 00:33:25,300
让他在矿井里死于黑肺病  我都不在乎
and let him die of black lung in a coal mine, for all I care.

553
00:33:25,300 --> 00:33:27,250
但我在乎你的经济
But I do care about your economy.

554
00:33:27,250 --> 00:33:29,190
你继续这么杀害受瞩目的商人
You keep killing high-profile businessmen

555
00:33:29,190 --> 00:33:30,300
查抄他们的财产
and seizing their assets.

556
00:33:30,300 --> 00:33:32,240
-那样不...  -你是说叛徒吧
- That's no-- - You mean, traitors?

557
00:33:32,660 --> 00:33:34,950
听着  我知道他们在密谋造反
Look, I am aware that they were plotting a coup,

558
00:33:34,950 --> 00:33:35,880
但那还是不...
but that still doesn't--

559
00:33:35,880 --> 00:33:38,990
是的  因为是你策划的
Yes, because you orchestrated it.

560
00:33:39,540 --> 00:33:42,410
-什么  -否则米尔金为什么要飞去美国
- Excuse me? - Why else would Milkin fly to America?

561
00:33:42,410 --> 00:33:44,490
这事跟我们完全无关
We had nothing to do with this.

562
00:33:45,340 --> 00:33:47,670
你...在约旦河谷的事上就跟我撒过谎
You... you lied to me about the Jordan Valley,

563
00:33:47,670 --> 00:33:49,950
你在迈克尔·科里根的事上跟我撒了谎
you lied to me about Michael Corrigan.

564
00:33:51,270 --> 00:33:53,610
我不是想要推翻你  维克多
I am not trying to replace you, Viktor.

565
00:33:53,610 --> 00:33:56,100
我是想帮你  但你也得帮我
I'm trying to help you. But you have to help me.

566
00:33:56,100 --> 00:33:59,220
石油减产这样的威胁不会好使的
These threats of reducing your oil production, it won't work.

567
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:01,920
你以为抬升能源价格会伤到我们
You think jacking up energy prices is gonna hurt us,

568
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:03,600
但那只是敲诈
but it's just extortion.

569
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:05,960
我不会向敲诈低头的
And I will not respond to extortion.

570
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,380
我可以把你的叛徒送回去
Now, I'll send your traitor back,

571
00:34:07,380 --> 00:34:08,330
但你不能再
but you've got to stop

572
00:34:08,340 --> 00:34:10,980
查抄公司  把人变没了
seizing companies and making people disappear.

573
00:34:10,980 --> 00:34:14,760
伊戈尔·米尔金比叛徒还糟糕  他是美国的傀儡
Igor Milkin is worse than a traitor. He's an American puppet.

574
00:34:14,970 --> 00:34:17,180
改朝换代  那才是敲诈
Regime change, that's extortion.

575
00:34:17,180 --> 00:34:20,150
是啊  但那是他们自己的行为  你是多虑了
Yes, but they acted on their own. You're being paranoid.

576
00:34:20,150 --> 00:34:22,060
送他回来  别开条件
Send him back. No terms.

577
00:34:22,060 --> 00:34:25,100
你如果不肯谈判  我们不会有进展的
We're not going to get anywhere if you're not willing to negotiate.

578
00:34:25,100 --> 00:34:26,020
那...
Well...

579
00:34:26,790 --> 00:34:28,450
我们没话可说了
then I believe we're finished.

580
00:34:28,450 --> 00:34:31,980
是没什么可说了  谢谢  总统先生
And I believe you're right. Thank you, Mr. President.

581
00:34:34,750 --> 00:34:37,920
把米尔金安置在安全地点  他哪都不能去
Put Milkin in a secure location. He's not going anywhere.

582
00:34:43,830 --> 00:34:44,900
米尔金先生
Mr. Milkin.

583
00:34:46,060 --> 00:34:47,420
请你跟我来
I need you to come with me.

584
00:34:47,420 --> 00:34:48,400
我们去哪
Where are we going?

585
00:34:49,090 --> 00:34:50,690
羁押设施
A detainment facility.

586
00:34:50,820 --> 00:34:52,240
我不是要被遣返吧
I'm not being deported, am I?

587
00:34:52,240 --> 00:34:54,930
不  我们要处理你的庇护请求
No, we're going to process your asylum request.

588
00:36:08,470 --> 00:36:09,440
克莱尔
Claire?

589
00:36:14,710 --> 00:36:17,430
如果你想抽烟  就抽吧
If you wanna smoke, you should smoke.

590
00:36:18,790 --> 00:36:20,380
我就是想抽一口
I only wanted one drag.

591
00:36:21,930 --> 00:36:26,520
他讨厌你以前拿着烟去马厩
He hated how you used to go down to the stables with your cigarettes.

592
00:36:28,330 --> 00:36:30,010
我不知道他知道这事
I didn't realize he knew.

593
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:33,790
他那么爱你  你杀人他都不会在乎
He adored you. You got away with murder.

594
00:36:36,010 --> 00:36:37,570
你一直没睡等着我吗
Did you wait up for me?

595
00:36:37,650 --> 00:36:40,100
不  是药的关系
No, it's the medication.

596
00:36:40,370 --> 00:36:44,190
让我整天都感觉疲惫  然后又整宿睡不着
Keeps me tired all day, and then I'm up all night.

597
00:36:45,830 --> 00:36:49,140
我...看了讲话
I... I watched the speech.

598
00:36:49,810 --> 00:36:51,250
你打算怎么办
What are you gonna do?

599
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:54,600
很晚了  母亲  我们早上再谈吧
It's late, Mother. Let's talk in the morning.

600
00:36:55,090 --> 00:36:59,910
对了  耳环真漂亮  我在电视上注意到了
By the way, those earrings are beautiful. I noticed 'em on TV.

601
00:37:01,630 --> 00:37:03,680
是弗兰西斯母亲的耳环
They're Francis' mother's earrings.

602
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:06,900
-貌似不止一克拉  -两克拉
- They look like they're over a carat. - Two carats.

603
00:37:07,310 --> 00:37:09,150
她肯定从谁那儿偷来的
No doubt she stole them from someone.

604
00:37:11,650 --> 00:37:15,270
安德伍德一家永远能让人吃惊
The Underwoods never cease to amaze.

605
00:37:15,330 --> 00:37:16,280
母亲
Mother...

606
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:19,760
我需要点钱
I'm going to need some money.

607
00:37:20,620 --> 00:37:22,030
给诊所吗  不是...
For the clinic? Isn't--

608
00:37:22,030 --> 00:37:25,200
150万  给莉安  还额外再需要一点
A million five for LeAnn and some on top of that.

609
00:37:25,740 --> 00:37:28,740
我以为你的竞选没戏了
Well, I thought your campaign was dead.

610
00:37:28,740 --> 00:37:31,470
是的  但我还是需要她为我工作
It is, but I still need her to work for me.

611
00:37:31,470 --> 00:37:34,790
但做什么呢  我可以向我的朋友借钱
But, what for? I mean, I can't ask my friends for money and--

612
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:35,910
我们的钱
Our money.

613
00:37:40,390 --> 00:37:42,780
你是指我的钱
You mean my money.

614
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:45,080
别跟我争
Don't fight me on this.

615
00:37:45,080 --> 00:37:46,840
爸爸会毫不犹豫地给我
Daddy would've done it, no questions asked.

616
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:50,180
是啊  我没他那么傻
Yes, well... I'm not as foolish as he was.

617
00:37:50,180 --> 00:37:52,190
那我只能卖掉地产了
Well, I'll just have to sell the estate.

618
00:37:52,190 --> 00:37:53,350
什么
You what?

619
00:37:53,350 --> 00:37:56,240
钱在信托里  但地产是在我名下
The money is in the trust, but the land is in my name.

620
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:59,330
-你不会敢的  -我在求你帮忙
- You wouldn't dare. - Well, I'm asking for your help.

621
00:37:59,330 --> 00:38:01,430
-如果你不肯  -帮忙
- If you refuse to give it-- - Help?

622
00:38:01,440 --> 00:38:05,010
我生病时你可完全没帮过我
You didn't lift a finger to help me when I got sick.

623
00:38:05,010 --> 00:38:06,620
你没告诉我你病了
You didn't tell me you were sick!

624
00:38:06,620 --> 00:38:08,880
因为你已经背弃了我
Because you had turned your back on me!

625
00:38:09,090 --> 00:38:12,020
你是那么让人失望
Oh, you are such a disappointment.

626
00:38:14,090 --> 00:38:17,680
你不希望我背着你卖掉房子  但我会的
You don't want me to sell this house out from under you, but I will.

627
00:38:21,190 --> 00:38:22,790
我是你母亲
I am the mother.

628
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:25,600
我是你母亲
I am the mother!

